Bworld redone w/out the portals and the black and white world. 

After seeing too many instances of individuals getting stuck together in portal destinations and humans getting bored because of zombies not being able to find the ladder out of bworld, I opted to remove all high traffic portals from the map, as well as remove the black and white room entirely.

This version features several redone campspots with the inclusion of a brand new one. The betterbworld is much more streamlined so people with an ounce of common sense will be able to navigate from one room to the other without much difficulty.

I also added volumetric lighting streaming thru the windows with dust particles. Thanks to Something for help with the lighting and http://www.fpsbanana.com/members/subs/131051 
for that recommendation, props!

Hi, i have just finished a map update. You might know the older version called: zm anotheruglyzmap v1e

**Changelog:**


-fixed the laser room (+ many improvements)


-new room with quicksand

**Mapfeatures:**


-64 spawns


-plenty of camp spots and traps


-a laser room!

-qubemaps + overview

Note:


In picture 2, you can see the console to configurate the laser room. There are three different options:


-3 lasers in a row (you can change the angle of each one of them)


-a fast laser _(only after 3 activations - there is a trigger inside the room)


-Laser grid _(only after 6 activations)

Laserroom:
<object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/1FC2s6TyG7w&hl=en"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/1FC2s6TyG7w&hl=en" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="425" height="344"></embed></object>

History:
I played this map a long time on my own zombie server. so i could see weak points and fix em.

Features:
-64 spawns
-mapoverview/radar
-camping spots with secret access
-camping spots with automatic defend-systems
-barricade rooms
-some secrets
-fair and balanced

About the Laserroom:
U cannot control the laser-defend system manual but its possible to activade/deactivate it.
There is a trigger inside this room, which activate the laser if some one walk through.
Timing:
After triggering the doors get closed for 5 seconds, while the lasers are running through the room. (reload time) 
If the doors open again, its possible to walk through the room for 5 seconds. (chance for zombies)
>Just be sure: the red light is on!!!<

It´s also possible to dodge the lasers. (crouch for the first laser and jump for the second one)


Recommend config
-reload
-zombie knockback 2-3
-zombie HP 3000-4000

please assess/rate
